        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3702328575" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8097800016014067580"><a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/329866.The_Dream_of_a_Ridiculous_Man' title='The Dream of a Ridiculous Man by Fyodor Dostoyevsky' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Dream Of A Ridiculous Man</a> by <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/3137322.Fyodor_Dostoyevsky' title='Fyodor Dostoyevsky' rel='nofollow noopener'>Fyodor Dostoyevsky</a><br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1608322296i/30554116._SX540_.jpg' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/>In this short story, the main character described his strange dream about happy land and people living in peace without desires or sins. That dream made him change from the idea of suicide and wander in love with life again. In these few pages, you will feel that another world has suddenly emerged in front of you that you might not expect! It&apos;s a delightful story that gives teaching about humanity. And at the same time, it criticizes evil works.</span>
  <span id="freeText8097800016014067580" style="display:none"><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/329866.The_Dream_of_a_Ridiculous_Man" title="The Dream of a Ridiculous Man by Fyodor Dostoyevsky" rel="nofollow noopener">The Dream Of A Ridiculous Man</a> by <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/3137322.Fyodor_Dostoyevsky" title="Fyodor Dostoyevsky" rel="nofollow noopener">Fyodor Dostoyevsky</a><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1608322296i/30554116._SX540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>In this short story, the main character described his strange dream about happy land and people living in peace without desires or sins. That dream made him change from the idea of suicide and wander in love with life again. In these few pages, you will feel that another world has suddenly emerged in front of you that you might not expect! It's a delightful story that gives teaching about humanity. And at the same time, it criticizes evil works.<br><blockquote>
  <i>Sorrow compressed my heart, and I felt I would die, and then . . . Well, then I woke up.</i>
</blockquote><br><i>Thoughtful.</i></span>
