    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_4009511921" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4009511921" />
    <a title="Swaroop" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/100264072-swaroop"><img alt="Swaroop" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1621672092p2/100264072.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4009511921?book_show_action=true">May 18, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Swaroop" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Swaroop" href="/user/show/100264072-swaroop">Swaroop</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4009511921" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4774953878055300088">Profound.<br/><br/>Fyodor Mikhailovich Dostoyevsky`s <i>The Dream of a Ridiculous Man</i> is indeed, ridiculously brilliant!<br/><br/>A man in a state of horrible despair is slipping into the pessimism of the terrible kind, starts feeling that there is no value of living anymore and nothing of purpose in this world, and decides that it is time to end his life. He sees around him and in the sky, all the signs to go ahead with his decision. When the man is looking at the stars confirming his plan, a little girl pulls him by</span>
  <span id="freeText4774953878055300088" style="display:none">Profound.<br><br>Fyodor Mikhailovich Dostoyevsky`s <i>The Dream of a Ridiculous Man</i> is indeed, ridiculously brilliant!<br><br>A man in a state of horrible despair is slipping into the pessimism of the terrible kind, starts feeling that there is no value of living anymore and nothing of purpose in this world, and decides that it is time to end his life. He sees around him and in the sky, all the signs to go ahead with his decision. When the man is looking at the stars confirming his plan, a little girl pulls him by the elbow asking for help, and everything changes! <br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1621787092i/31379269._SY540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>[Fyodor Mikhailovich Dostoyevsky, Portrait by Vasily Perov, 1871.]<br><br><i>"Dreams, as we all know, are very queer things."<br><br>"Dreams seem to be spurred on not by reason but by desire, not by the head but by the heart, and yet what complicated tricks my reason has played sometimes in dreams, what utterly incomprehensible things happen to it!"</i><br><br>This is a <b>wonderful and thought-provoking</b> short story in which Dostoyevsky shows that all it takes to discover the meaning of life, faith in humanity and the value of this world, is a dream! <br><br>The lonely man postpones his decision because he feels guilty of mistreating and not helping the girl. He falls asleep on his chair and dreams of, after killing himself, going to another earth that is physically similar to this earth but is highly moral and ethical. The man happens to 'corrupt' that earth with his knowledge, eventually wakes up grief-stricken and takes a decision to live the rest of this life teaching the truth he has learnt in his dream. <br><br>It felt as if the man has 'abandoned' his pessimism and darkness on the other earth. When a person lets go of the darkness, all he is left with is optimism and the light. Well, it may not be as easy to let go of the sadness and depression, but it surely has the message that there is always light at the end of the tunnel. When we find a purpose or a meaningful act to do, the cover of darkness lifts from our lives. This is the 'truth' that was clear as daylight to Dostoyevsky`s lonely man after the dream, and it is time to tell others about it, as they have not yet seen it. <br><br><i><br>"And so there is life beyond the grave"<br><br><blockquote><b>"They desired nothing and were at peace; they did not aspire to knowledge of life as we aspire to understand it, because their lives were full." </b></blockquote>
<br>"An yet, you know, all are making for the same goal, all are striving in the same direction anyway, from the sage to the lowest robber, only by different roads." </i><br><br>==========<br><br><i>Love my Life</i> – Robbie Williams <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://youtu.be/j4ggyO-OFXU">https://youtu.be/j4ggyO-OFXU</a><br><br>Tether your soul to me<br>I will never let go completely<br>One day your hands will be<br>Strong enough to hold me<br>I might not be there for all your battles<br>But you'll win them eventually<br>I pray that I'm giving you all that matters<br>So one day you'll say to me<br><br>I love my life<br>I am powerful<br>I am beautiful<br>I am free<br>I love my life<br>I am wonderful<br>I am magical<br>I am me<br>I love my life<br><br>I am not my mistakes<br>And God knows, I've made a few<br>I started to question the angels<br>And the answer they gave was you<br>I cannot promise there won't be sadness<br>I wish I could take it from you<br>But you'll find the courage to face the madness<br>And sing it because it's true<br><br>I love my life<br>I am powerful<br>I am beautiful<br>I am free<br>I love my life<br>I am wonderful<br>I am magical<br>I am me<br>I love my life<br>Find the others<br>With hearts<br>Like yours<br>Run far, run free<br>I'm with you<br>I love my life<br>I am powerful<br>I am beautiful<br>I am free<br>I love my life<br>I am wonderful<br>I am magical<br>I am me<br><br><i>
  <b>I love my life<br>I am powerful<br>I am beautiful<br>I am free<br>I love my life<br>I am wonderful<br>I am magical<br>I am me<br>I love my life<br>And finally<br>I'm where I want to be</b>
</i><br><br>© Farrell Music Ltd.</span>
