<div id="review_2749982238" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2749982238" />
    <a title="Supreeth" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/64325592-supreeth"><img alt="Supreeth" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1613925764p2/64325592.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2749982238?book_show_action=true">Mar 14, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Supreeth" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Supreeth" href="/user/show/64325592-supreeth">Supreeth</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/30115055-the-dream-of-a-ridiculous-man">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/64325592-supreeth?shelf=2019">2019</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/64325592-supreeth?shelf=existentialism-nihilism">existentialism-nihilism</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/64325592-supreeth?shelf=philosophy-psychology">philosophy-psychology</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/64325592-supreeth?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/64325592-supreeth?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/64325592-supreeth?shelf=russian">russian</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/64325592-supreeth?shelf=dostoyevskiana">dostoyevskiana</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2749982238" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14063908757022646540">Dostoyevsky&apos;s ideas are hard to be labeled as any sort of philosophy, they&apos;re dispersed in a broad spectrum. He has this ability to portray suffering as some sort of delicious sexy looking dish you&apos;d crave for. And all that in twenty-six pages. But suffering is something he talks about a whole lot. He rips the idea of <i>&apos;the paradise&apos;</i>. If you&apos;re rich and charming and have a bunch of close friends who&apos;d basically nod at everything you say, have good sex, never hungry, never agitated, completely acc</span>
  <span id="freeText14063908757022646540" style="display:none">Dostoyevsky's ideas are hard to be labeled as any sort of philosophy, they're dispersed in a broad spectrum. He has this ability to portray suffering as some sort of delicious sexy looking dish you'd crave for. And all that in twenty-six pages. But suffering is something he talks about a whole lot. He rips the idea of <i>'the paradise'</i>. If you're rich and charming and have a bunch of close friends who'd basically nod at everything you say, have good sex, never hungry, never agitated, completely accepted and respected, and everyone's optimistic and kind and all that—it doesn't even seem that interesting. What's the whole point? So what's your thing now, just stay happy forever? Perhaps man is attracted to 'suffering' so much that he actually creates them, I guess that's the reason the typical problems of a typical first world citizen and a third world citizen differ so much.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14063908757022646540" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


