<span id="freeTextContainer9800069986277302122">Faith. This is what emanated from this story the most for me. The faith that love will one day rule every man’s heart. The faith that meaning will be discovered in every action a man performs. The faith that human beings can find and live in truth.<br/><br/>A remarkable short story in that it captured my desire to believe in something true, in the goodness of being and the value of experience whether witnessed or imagined. I loved Dostoyevsky’s description of the man’s dream, of being grasped by a force w</span>
  <span id="freeText9800069986277302122" style="display:none">Faith. This is what emanated from this story the most for me. The faith that love will one day rule every man’s heart. The faith that meaning will be discovered in every action a man performs. The faith that human beings can find and live in truth.<br /><br />A remarkable short story in that it captured my desire to believe in something true, in the goodness of being and the value of experience whether witnessed or imagined. I loved Dostoyevsky’s description of the man’s dream, of being grasped by a force which takes him out of the earth and soaring through the sky to finally land where life is different, where people care for one another unconditionally and can communicate with mother nature in dimensions completely unknown in his previous experience. Beautiful ideas, beautifully conveyed. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="9800069986277302122" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
