<div id="review_738512744" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/738512744" />
    <a title="Anne  Zappa" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15738127-anne-zappa"><img alt="Anne  Zappa" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1469268311p2/15738127.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/738512744?book_show_action=true">Oct 10, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Anne  Zappa" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Anne  Zappa" href="/user/show/15738127-anne-zappa">Anne  Zappa</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer738512744" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer896071605489966884">This book is about an <i>experience</i> and not a <i>notion</i>, an experience of spiritual enlightenment that I think Dostoevsky had, which he wanted vicariously conveyed through this short story.<br/><br/>The ridiculous man dreams of dying, then gets resurrected or reaches some kind of an afterlife, he lands on this <s>Extra Virgin</s> Greek Island Paradise where everyone is <s>stoned</s> happy, loved &amp; peaceful. People are experiencing eternal bliss but as they consort with our protagonist, they get corrupt, get thrilled by the f</span>
  <span id="freeText896071605489966884" style="display:none">This book is about an <i>experience</i> and not a <i>notion</i>, an experience of spiritual enlightenment that I think Dostoevsky had, which he wanted vicariously conveyed through this short story.<br /><br />The ridiculous man dreams of dying, then gets resurrected or reaches some kind of an afterlife, he lands on this <s>Extra Virgin</s> Greek Island Paradise where everyone is <s>stoned</s> happy, loved &amp; peaceful. People are experiencing eternal bliss but as they consort with our protagonist, they get corrupt, get thrilled by the first lie they create, this debauchery grows into further evil, proliferating into a world akin to the one we are living in today.<br /><br />Awakening from his sleep the ridiculous man realizes that he had been the cause for the downfall of our species, hence is obliged to preach the ideals of utopia he had encountered in his dream. This bringing direction &amp; purpose to his life.</span>
  <a data-text-id="896071605489966884" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


