  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1347897390" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1347897390" />
    <a title="Soycd" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16638128-soycd"><img alt="Soycd" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1527549268p2/16638128.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1347897390?book_show_action=true">Jul 28, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Soycd" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Soycd" href="/user/show/16638128-soycd">Soycd</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16638128-soycd?shelf=2016-1">2016-1</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1347897390" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7295201088847088887"> <br/><i>A dream! What is a dream? And is not our life a dream?</i><br/><br/>The dream of a Ridiculous Man is the story of a man who has become disenchanted with the world and is considering suicide. One day he was going home when he was approached by a little girl who asked him for help and he refused to acknowledge her. After that he resumed his walk until he noticed something that caught his eye:<br/><br/><i>The sky was horribly dark, but one could distinctly see tattered clouds, and between them fathomless black patches. Sudd</i></span>
  <span id="freeText7295201088847088887" style="display:none"> <br /><i>A dream! What is a dream? And is not our life a dream?</i><br /><br />The dream of a Ridiculous Man is the story of a man who has become disenchanted with the world and is considering suicide. One day he was going home when he was approached by a little girl who asked him for help and he refused to acknowledge her. After that he resumed his walk until he noticed something that caught his eye:<br /><br /><i>The sky was horribly dark, but one could distinctly see tattered clouds, and between them fathomless black patches. Suddenly I noticed in one of these patches a star, and began watching it intently. That was because that star had given me an idea: I decided to kill myself that night. </i><br /><br />He entered his house and pulled out his gun. He started to think about the little girl until he fell asleep and had a dream that would have a profound impact on him. In that dream he is laying in a coffin after having shot himself in the heart. After that he sees someone taking him out of his coffin. His eyes go black and he is surrounded by a star shinning in the darkness. They travel through space until they reach destination in a planet that looks exactly like Earth.<br /><br /><i>The people of this happy land came to me of themselves, they surrounded me, kissed me. Their faces were radiant with the light of reason and fullness of a serenity that comes of perfect understanding, but those faces were gay; in their words and voices there was a note of childlike joy. Oh, from the first moment, from the first glance at them, I understood it all! It was the earth untarnished by the Fall; on it lived people who had not sinned. </i><br /><br />After that the people who lived there <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[get corrupted, and the protagonist offers to sacrifice himself to redeem them for their sins. He wakes up from the dream as a new man and decides to help the little girl who approached him at the beginning of the story. <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br />A lot of things were going through my mind when I was reading this. The first one is the religious symbolism in the story. There is the representation of the Garden of Eden, the possibility of suffering to achieve redemption, the idea that the actions of one man can have a huge impact on others and the existence of an afterlife. I think the insistence on the veracity of the dream is an analogy of faith; you have to be willing to believe in things even without proof. The star on the sky may be a representation of fate and hope. The protagonist is a lost soul who needs to reach out to other people to try to find that light amidst the darkness that will allow him to find his own Eden, a place of happiness and understanding.<br /><br />There is something fascinating about Dostoevsky that makes me keep going back to his books: there is so much darkness in his work but the light is always stronger. The message that permeates his whole body of work is his belief in redemption and finding good in people who have lost their way. <br /><br />Reading this author feels like reaching the Eden he describes, it makes you want to become a better person. And after you put the book down you wake up from your own dream and realize that it has been a life changing experience for you too. <br /><br /><i>The chief thing is to love others like yourself, that's the chief thing, and that's everything; nothing else is wanted — you will find out at once how to arrange it all. And yet it's an old truth which has been told and retold a billion times — but it has not formed part of our lives!</i><br /><br />After I finished reading I watched this amazing animation of the story. It was made by Russian director Alexandr Petrov: <br /><br /><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jIr7cs6eEAs" rel="nofollow noopener">Dream of a Ridiculous Man</a></span>
  <a data-text-id="7295201088847088887" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


